&lt;p&gt;An administrative assistant is required to provide telephone and data system support to the Aylesbury Adult Community Healthcare Team based at Stoke Mandeville Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be computer literate and able to use excel and word. Candidates must have an excellent telephone manner.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The team delivers services to patients in their own homes and the administrator acts as first point of contact for service users and referrers to the service. You will enjoy the challenge of working in a busy environment and have the ability to stay calm under pressure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team provides a 7 day service and therefore the successful applicant will be required to work occasional weekends and bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Diana Bunce&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Community Team Lead diana.bunce@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or Jan Ferry 01296 566090&lt;/p&gt;
